<div id="tour_items_bottom_blocks">
    <!-- TOUR INTRODUCTION -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_introduction_bottom"  style="">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Centralize Communication</h2>
        <p>activeCollab&reg; will gather all the people that are important to your business and help them work together. It will also keep all of your data and records, negotiations and discussion, and documents and files all in one place.</p>
        <p>All your project data will always be just one click away.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Manage Projects</h2>
        <p>Organize your efforts into projects and gather people around them. activeCollab&reg; lets you define the key points in the project, assign tasks, track progress, share files and discuss the entire process.</p>
        <p>Get projects done with less management and more communication.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Mobile Interface</h2>
        <p>When you are away from your computer, you can use your mobile phone to access activeCollab&reg;. It will automatically detect that you are using a mobile device and serve content optimized for smaller screens and less bandwidth.</p>
        <p>Thanks to mobile interface, your data is always available.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- BRING EVERYONE ABOARD -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_bring_everyone_aboard_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>No Limits</h2>
        <p>When we say “Bring Everyone Aboard” we really mean it! You can invite all the people you are working with to join you in activeCollab&reg;, without any quantitative limitations.</p>
        <p>Together you can work on an unlimited number of projects, without restrictions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Roles and Permissions</h2>
        <p>There are two types of permissions in activeCollab&reg;:</p>
        <p>First are system permissions that define what user can do on a system level, like log in or access administration.</p>
        <p>Second type are project permissions that give or restrict access to specific sections in a particular project. Users can have different roles in different projects.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Data Privacy</h2>
        <p>activeCollab&reg; is designed to give you full control even when you include everyone in your workspace.</p>
        <p>People will see only projects they are working on. On top of that, you can mark some discussions and tasks so only members of your team can see them while your clients will not be aware of their existance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR MANAGE PROJECTS -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_managing_projects_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Groups and Clients</h2>
        <p>Large number of projects and people involved can create disorder and confusion. That&#146;s why you can organize all your projects in project groups. Additionally, each project can have a client.</p>
        <p>When properly sorted, you can easily access projects per group or per client.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Milestones</h2>
        <p>Milestones are important dates in a project. They can be a single day or a time range.</p>
        <p>Common milestones are launch dates, important meetings or reviews, presentations to a client, development iterations, etc.</p>
        <p>Use milestones to divide big projects into manageable steps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Tickets, Checklists, Tasks?</h2>
        <p>Tickets, checklists and tasks will bring your idea to life one step at a time.</p>
        <p>Tickets are big tasks that can be added to milestones, divided into smaller tasks and discussed. Checklists are similar, but they do not support comments and attachments. Instead, they behave more like good old todo lists.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR INVOICING -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_invoicing_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Your Projects + Invoicing</h2>
        <p>It's great to have your project management tool integrated with your billings. This way, you can create and send invoices while collaborating with your clients, from the data you already have: time logs and tickets.</p>
        <p>When an invoice is created from a time log, activeCollab&reg; automatically takes care of the status of all associated time records - from billable to paid.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Brandable PDF Invoices</h2>
        <p>When issuing an invoice, activeCollab sends a PDF with all information that your client needs in order to make a payment: total amount, payment instructions, tax information and other.</p>
        <p>All PDF documents sent by the system are branded with your corporate colors and logo, and contain information about your company.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>... and More!</h2>
        <p>On top of that, activeCollab&reg; invoicing has many smaller features that make your day-to-day financial operation easier:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Have activeCollab&reg; to automatically generate invoice numbers for you</li>
          <li>If you frequently invoice specific products and services, then just create a template</li>
          <li>Bill your customers in their countryʼs currency and issue invoices in their native language</li>
          <li>Define as many tax rates as you need</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR TRACK TIME -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_track_time_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Time Tracking</h2>
        <p>Time is important, especially if you charge your clients per hour. activeCollab&reg; lets you track how much time is spent on each project or task as well as make a disctinction between time that is billable and the time that is not.</p>
        <p>Data collected this way can be used to charge your clients or pay your employees.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Reports</h2>
        <p>activeCollab&reg; offers a way to filter all the time data you and your users logged. You can filter it by person who tracked the time, day it was logged for, status and project.</p>
        <p>Time reports can be saved and executed each time you need them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Export and Integration</h2>
        <p>Time report results can be exported in CSV format, and easily imported in any spreadsheet tool, like Microsoft Excel. These tools can be used to further manipulate the data.</p>
        <p>Using specialized desktop applications, you can track your time and have it automatically logged into the system through the API.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR SHARE FILES -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_sharing_files_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Project Files</h2>
        <p>People working on a project can upload unlimited number of related files. Project members will be able to download and discuss uploaded files.</p>
        <p>Using visibility property, you can even hide some of the files from your clients and have them available to member of your team only.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Version Tracking</h2>
        <p>When you upload a file for your associates to work on, changes they make will be tracked as new versions of that file. This way everybody can see how a file evolves and what direction it takes. Plus, everyone can comment and express opinion about the process.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Global Documents</h2>
        <p>Some files need to be available globally. Because of that, we added Documents in the latest activeCollab&reg; edition. Documents are global files that are independent from any particular project and everybody can see them.</p>
        <p>Just like project files, you can mark some of the documents as Private and have them available to the members of your team only.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR EMAIL INTEGRATION -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_email_integration_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Always up to Date</h2>
        <p>Email is one of the best ways to keep up with the projects. That's why activeCollab&reg; will send an email notification to project members when events such as new task creation, new comment or file version occure.</p>
        <p>The content of notification emails can be customized by system administrators.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Incoming Mail</h2>
        <p>Since version 2, activeCollab&reg; allows you to post a comment by replying on email notifications you received. If system receives a message that is not a reply to a notification, it will automatically create a new ticket or discussion based on it.</p>
        <p>System that handles incoming messages has full support for reading files attached to them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Email is Convenient</h2>
        <p>Everybody knows how to use email. By having ability to send and receive email it's more likely that your clients and employees will adopt the system. Instead of a sudden switch to a new way of working, they can continue to use the tools they are familar with.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR EXTEND AND INTEGRATE -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_extend_and_customize_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>The Look and Feel</h2>
        <p>One of the first thing most people do after they purchase activeCollab&reg; license is change the look and feel of the application to meet their visual identity.</p>
        <p>Be creative and make it feel like home for you and your associates. It will make a good impression on your clients, too!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Modules</h2>
        <p>activeCollab&reg; is an open and extensible system. By adding different Modules and Plugins to the application you can extend its features and make it fit your needs and demands.</p>
        <p>Modules extend the application from the inside and have a full access to all of its resources.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>API</h2>
        <p>API stands for Application Programming Interface. Basically, it means that other applications can communicate with your activeCollab&reg; installation in standardized way.</p>
        <p>API can be used to read or post the data from and to the system.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- TOUR KEEP CONTROL -->
    <div class="tour_item_bottom_block" id="tour_keep_control_bottom" style="display:none">
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Host it on Your Server</h2>
        <p>activeCollab&reg; puts you in charge and give you full control over the system. Host it on your own server, web site, or local network, it&#146;s up to you. The important thing is that it&#146;s completely your decision.</p>
        <p>activeCollab&reg; lets you have full control over your data and security settings.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Full Source Code</h2>
        <p>Installation package includes full, unencrypted source code. If you wish to make some changes to the system and make it fit your need, you're free to do that.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content_column">
        <h2>Flexible Permissions</h2>
        <p>Keep your data safe by defining roles for your users. Roles work on system and project level. Each user has one system role that controls his access permissions. On top of that, user can have different roles in different projects that control which project section he has access to.</p>
        <p>Data marked as Private is top secret and exposed only to people with special privileges.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
